          "tz": 120
        },
        "subject": "LU-4330 lnet: Allocate MEs and small MDs in own kmem_caches",
        "message": "LU-4330 lnet: Allocate MEs and small MDs in own kmem_caches\n\nAs part of LU-3848 and LU-4330, it has been discovered that LNET\nMEs and small MDs (<=128 Bytes) are allocated in <size-128> kmem_cache\nand thus can suffer quite frequent corruptions, from other modules or\nKernel parts, that occur there. To avoid this, MEs and small-MDs\nspecific kmem_cache have been created.\n\nThis patch was the earlier and original version of master patch :\nLustre-change: http://review.whamcloud.com/18586/\n\nSigned-off-by: Bruno Faccini <bruno.faccini@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I92fafa49591a5379f52545ee73b6084140ff3ca3\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b2_1"
    }
  },
